parameters.name: duration
parameters.description:
The duration is the number of seconds from start of the first mode     
      until start of the last mode.  Duration is related to the length of an 
      instrument cycle.  Several different spin modes are required to gather 
      all of the data necessary to compute these parameters.  The timing     
      was variable, dependent on telemetry rate and compressibility of the   
      data, so duration varies considerably.

parameters.name: mode
parameters.description:
This column gives the spin mode of the instrument during the sample.   
      Refer to the instrument paper for the complete definition of each      
      mode.

parameters.name: density
parameters.description: Number density (1/cm^3) of the heavy ion component of the plasma.

parameters.name: Temperature
parameters.description: Temperature (eV) of the heavy ion component of the plasma.

parameters.name: Vx
parameters.description:
X component of the plasma velocity vector in inertial rotor coordiantes
      (despun spacecraft coordinates).

parameters.name: Vy
parameters.description:
Y component of the plasma velocity vector in inertial rotor coordiantes
      (despun spacecraft coordinates).

parameters.name: Vz
parameters.description:
Z component of the plasma velocity vector in inertial rotor coordiantes
      (despun spacecraft coordinates).

parameters.name: density error
parameters.description: One sigma error in the number density parameter.

parameters.name: Temperature error
parameters.description: One sigma error in the temperature parameter.

parameters.name: Vx error
parameters.description: One sigma error in the Vx parameter.

parameters.name: Vy error
parameters.description: One sigma error in the Vy parameter.

parameters.name: Vz error
parameters.description: One sigma error in the Vz parameter.
